A look from inside one of the three new control rooms in Blue Devil Tower during a men's lacrosse broadcast.
Fast forward to the start of the 2016 season, a glistening Blue Devil Tower opened to the public.
"We heard the buzz about the ACC Network happening, and we were ahead of the curve," Chad Lampman, executive director of Blue Devil Network, said.
The network, which syndicates games nationwide but primarily reaches areas within the Southeast, will go off the air once the ACC Network takes over in August.
But as part of the ACC Network deal, the league locked in its TV rights with ESPN through the 2035-36 academic year.